Glance an ATA model

Source: R/fable_ata.R
glance.ATA.Rd

Glance an ATA model

# S3 method for ATA
glance(x, ...)

Arguments

x

An estimated model.

...

Unused.

Value

A one row tibble summarising the model's fit.

Examples

library(fable.ata)
as_tsibble(USAccDeaths) %>%
  model(ata = AutoATA(value ~ trend("A") + season("M"))) %>% glance()
#> # A tibble: 1 × 11
#>   .model sigma2 loglik   AIC  AICc   BIC    MSE   MAE sMAPE  MASE      OWA
#>   <chr>   <dbl>  <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>    <dbl>
#> 1 ata    66085.  -553. 1120. 1122. 1136. 66085.  201.  2.27 0.102 0.000599
